cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper describes the development of a self-driving algorithm for a race car. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the algorithm uses a single camera as input for inferring car steering angles. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also relevant as the paper discusses the challenges associated with training a deep neural network. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper explores the engineering challenges associated with the deployment of the system in the real world.
